t\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Bellows sealed globe valves are a specific type of globe valve designed with a bellows seal to provide additional protection against leakage, particularly in applications involving hazardous or corrosive fluids, or where fugitive emissions must be minimized.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p><strong>Design and Construction:<\/strong><\/p><p>\u2022 Bellow sealed globe valves feature a bellows assembly that is integrated into the bonnet of the valve. The bellows typically consist of a series of convolutions made from a flexible metal such as stainless steel.<\/p><p>\u2022 This bellows assembly creates a hermetic seal between the valve stem and the bonnet, preventing the process fluid from coming into contact with the stem or escaping to the atmosphere.<\/p><p>\u2022 The bellows design also compensates for thermal expansion and contraction, ensuring reliable sealing even under fluctuating temperature conditions.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p><strong>Applications:<\/strong><\/p><p>\u2022 Bellow sealed globe valves are commonly used in industries such as chemical processing, pharmaceuticals, petrochemicals, oil and gas, power generation, and refineries, where leakage prevention and environmental safety are paramount.<\/p><p>\u2022 They are suitable for handling a wide range of fluids, including corrosive chemicals, toxic gases, and volatile substances. Bellow sealed globe valves are often used in processes involving cryogenic temperatures, high pressures, or hazardous materials.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p><strong>Standards and Certifications:<\/strong><\/p><p>\u2022 Bellow sealed globe valves are manufactured in accordance with industry standards and specifications such as API (American Petroleum Institute), ASME (American Society of Mechanical Engineers), ASTM (American Society for Testing and Materials), ANSI (American National Standards Institute), and other relevant standards.